The paper discusses the degree distribution of deep neural networks, which is a topic closely related to network science and graph theory. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also discusses the learning process of deep neural networks, which falls under the category of machine learning. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely category. Additionally, the paper discusses the properties of deep neural networks, which is related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also proposes a model to explain the evolution of network topology, which is related to systems and control (cs.SY) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
